<subSubSection box="[199,1225,1159,1184]" pageId="15" pageNumber="286" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,151,1293]" box="[199,1225,1159,1184]" pageId="15" pageNumber="286">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,1159,1184]" pageId="15" pageNumber="286">Etymology</emphasis>
. Latin, 
<taxonomicName box="[413,509,1159,1184]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Meridiotroctes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obliquus">
<emphasis box="[413,509,1159,1184]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="286">obliquus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
= oblique, inclined; allusive to the oblique dark spots on elytra.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="286" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,151,1293]" pageId="15" pageNumber="286">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[209,325,1196,1221]" pageId="15" pageNumber="286">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[334,605,1196,1221]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Meridiotroctes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obliquus">
<emphasis box="[334,605,1196,1221]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="286">Meridiotroctes obliquus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the other species of the genus, mainly by the oblique dark spots at distal half of elytra. It also differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[721,869,1231,1256]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Meridiotroctes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicristata">
<emphasis box="[721,869,1231,1256]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="286">M. bicristata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[931,1106,1231,1256]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Meridiotroctes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="286" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="meridionale">
<emphasis box="[931,1106,1231,1256]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="286">M. meridionale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the truncate elytral apex (rounded in these species).
</paragraph>
